    <string name="home_intro_body"><![CDATA[
        <br>
        <h3>1. Introduction</h3>
        <p>Uses infrared or laser pulse sensors to calculate the Time of Flight (ToF) of photons reflected back to measure distance. No ARCore support needed, but ensure your device has the sensor. Some objects (black absorbing objects, transparent glass) may not reflect signals accurately.</p>
        <p>Range &amp; Accuracy: Depends on phone hardware. Some may be limited to &#60;80cm or &#62;3m. Units are generally in millimeters.</p>
        <br>

        <h3>2. User Guide</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Crosshair:</b> The center crosshair marks the measurement point. Long press to drag it to align with specific objects.</li><br>
            <li><b>Lock:</b> Tap the lock icon to freeze interaction and prevent accidental movement.</li><br>
            <li><b>Pause/Resume:</b> Tap the pause button to freeze the current reading. Distance, angle, and time are automatically saved to history.</li><br>
            <li><b>Timer:</b> Tap the timer icon (top-left) to set a delay. Useful for selfies or measuring wall distance when you can\'t see the screen. Auto-pauses and saves data when time is up.</li>
        </ul>
        <br>

        <h3>3. Data &amp; Export</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><b>History:</b> Records are saved automatically on pause (can be set to manual). Includes distance, V/H angles, and compass heading. Long press to delete, tap to add notes.</li><br>
            <li><b>Units:</b> Tap the ruler icon in history to switch between mm/cm/m.</li><br>
            <li><b>Export:</b> In settings, export records as Excel (.xlsx), CSV, or Markdown, or share directly to other apps.</li>
        </ul>
        <br>

        <h3>4. Tools</h3>
        <p>Access the Toolbox from the menu to use various sensor-based tools: Distance, Angle, Level, Compass, Altitude, Barometer, Decibel Meter, Light Meter, etc. More features coming soon.</p>
        <br>

        <h3>5. About</h3>
        <p>This app utilizes phone sensors to provide convenient depth measurement tools. Open source and free for offline use.</p>
        <p>Github: <a href="https://github.com/hikwin/ToFRangefinder">https://github.com/hikwin/ToFRangefinder</a></p>
        <p>License: Apache License 2.0</p>
        <br>
    ]]></string>

